WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.170 --> 00:00:01.840
Why my brain works differently,

1
00:00:02.049 --> 00:00:04.030
what you don't see behind my behavior,

2
00:00:04.130 --> 00:00:05.489
when you see my behavior,

3
00:00:05.650 --> 00:00:07.449
it might look like I'm overreacting.

4
00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:10.789
Like I go from calm to angry too quickly.

5
00:00:11.600 --> 00:00:13.770
Or I shut down for no clear reason.

6
00:00:14.659 --> 00:00:19.040
But what you may not realize is my brain has been shaped by what I've been through.

7
00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:22.780
It didn't develop in the same way you might expect.

8
00:00:23.610 --> 00:00:24.639
When I was younger,

9
00:00:24.889 --> 00:00:26.430
things weren't always safe.

10
00:00:27.239 --> 00:00:28.120
There was stress,

11
00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:29.600
sometimes a lot of it.

12
00:00:30.409 --> 00:00:34.509
And not always someone there to help me feel calm or make sense of things.

13
00:00:35.400 --> 00:00:36.759
So my brain adapted.

14
00:00:37.560 --> 00:00:38.419
It had to

15
00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:42.069
It focused on survival instead of feeling safe.

16
00:00:42.880 --> 00:00:45.369
There's a part of my brain that looks out for danger.

17
00:00:46.240 --> 00:00:47.779
Mine works really well.

18
00:00:48.689 --> 00:00:49.830
May be too well

19
00:00:50.549 --> 00:00:52.189
It notices small things,

20
00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:53.430
changes in tone,

21
00:00:53.669 --> 00:00:54.650
body language,

22
00:00:54.750 --> 00:00:56.310
the atmosphere in a room.

23
00:00:56.909 --> 00:00:59.060
Things that might not seem important to you,

24
00:00:59.270 --> 00:00:59.860
but to me,

25
00:00:59.990 --> 00:01:01.069
they feel important.

26
00:01:01.869 --> 00:01:01.880
Because

27
00:01:02.270 --> 00:01:06.269
my brain has learned that small changes can mean something bigger is coming.

28
00:01:07.339 --> 00:01:08.510
So I stay ready

29
00:01:09.629 --> 00:01:10.779
Even when I don't mean to.

30
00:01:11.559 --> 00:01:13.099
And when something shifts,

31
00:01:13.239 --> 00:01:15.300
my body reacts before I can think.

32
00:01:16.069 --> 00:01:18.370
I don't get time to pause and work it out.

33
00:01:19.180 --> 00:01:20.440
I might get angry

34
00:01:21.230 --> 00:01:22.260
Really quickly

35
00:01:22.870 --> 00:01:25.569
Or I might walk away before things get worse.

36
00:01:26.349 --> 00:01:27.379
Or sometimes

37
00:01:28.099 --> 00:01:30.000
I just go quiet and switch off.

38
00:01:30.750 --> 00:01:32.750
That's not me choosing to be difficult.

39
00:01:33.610 --> 00:01:35.589
That's my body trying to protect me.

40
00:01:36.309 --> 00:01:37.809
The thinking part of my brain,

41
00:01:38.150 --> 00:01:40.220
the bit that helps me make sense of things,

42
00:01:40.459 --> 00:01:42.809
it doesn't always get a chance to catch up.

43
00:01:43.559 --> 00:01:46.669
Especially when everything inside me feels too much.

44
00:01:47.599 --> 00:01:49.980
So when you ask me to explain myself

45
00:01:50.120 --> 00:01:51.599
or tell me to calm down.

46
00:01:52.430 --> 00:01:53.830
I might not be able to.

47
00:01:54.709 --> 00:01:55.910
Not in that moment.

48
00:01:56.699 --> 00:01:59.160
It's like everything is happening too fast.

49
00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:02.389
What you see as behavior is often me trying

50
00:02:02.389 --> 00:02:05.410
to cope with something I don't fully understand myself.

51
00:02:06.129 --> 00:02:08.449
And it's not just in those big moments.

52
00:02:09.149 --> 00:02:10.288
It's all the time

53
00:02:11.139 --> 00:02:12.500
My brain stays busy.

54
00:02:13.360 --> 00:02:14.059
Listening

55
00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:15.509
Watching

56
00:02:16.369 --> 00:02:16.929
Checking

57
00:02:17.770 --> 00:02:19.309
Even when nothing's wrong.

58
00:02:20.160 --> 00:02:22.160
That makes things harder for me.

59
00:02:22.679 --> 00:02:24.000
Focusing on tasks.

60
00:02:24.960 --> 00:02:26.259
Remembering things.

61
00:02:27.059 --> 00:02:28.199
Trusting people

62
00:02:29.309 --> 00:02:30.899
Sometimes I want to get things right,

63
00:02:31.149 --> 00:02:33.669
but I feel overwhelmed before I even start.

64
00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:36.279
And that can look like I'm not trying.

65
00:02:37.089 --> 00:02:37.789
But I am

66
00:02:38.539 --> 00:02:40.639
It just doesn't feel easy.

67
00:02:41.220 --> 00:02:42.500
Please understand that.

68
00:02:43.279 --> 00:02:43.289
Because

69
00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:45.820
when I feel rushed or told off,

70
00:02:46.039 --> 00:02:47.559
or like I've got it wrong again.

71
00:02:48.350 --> 00:02:51.369
It adds to everything that's already going on inside.

72
00:02:52.169 --> 00:02:54.729
It makes my brain feel even less safe.

73
00:02:55.470 --> 00:02:56.830
And then I react again.

74
00:02:57.679 --> 00:02:58.910
But when you stay calm,

75
00:02:59.080 --> 00:03:00.279
even when I'm not,

76
00:03:01.110 --> 00:03:02.660
When your voice doesn't change,

77
00:03:02.830 --> 00:03:04.970
when you don't come too close too quickly,

78
00:03:05.149 --> 00:03:06.750
when you give me a bit of space.

79
00:03:07.639 --> 00:03:08.970
Something feels different.

80
00:03:09.839 --> 00:03:11.240
I don't always show it.

81
00:03:12.059 --> 00:03:13.100
But I notice

82
00:03:13.919 --> 00:03:16.679
My body starts to slow down just a bit.

83
00:03:17.529 --> 00:03:19.460
That's when I can start to think again.

84
00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:23.539
That's when the thinking part of my brain begins to come back.

85
00:03:24.270 --> 00:03:25.169
And I can listen

86
00:03:25.369 --> 00:03:26.990
and maybe even talk.

87
00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:29.369
What I need from you is time.

88
00:03:30.229 --> 00:03:31.259
Consistency

89
00:03:32.050 --> 00:03:34.449
Not guessing what version of you I'm going to get.

90
00:03:35.289 --> 00:03:38.110
I need you to mean what you say and stay the same,

91
00:03:38.210 --> 00:03:39.309
even when I'm not.

92
00:03:40.270 --> 00:03:41.889
Because behind my behavior

93
00:03:41.990 --> 00:03:45.550
is a brain that learned to survive before it learned to feel safe.

94
00:03:46.289 --> 00:03:49.160
And when you respond in a way that helps me feel safe,

95
00:03:49.369 --> 00:03:52.169
you're helping me do something I'm still learning how to do.

96
00:03:52.979 --> 00:03:54.240
You're helping me feel

97
00:03:55.110 --> 00:03:56.410
Not just react